1 and 12 and "},{"code":"day","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"between 1 and 28, 29, 30 or 31 depending on the month and the year.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"hour","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must be between 0 and 23 and ","type":"text"},{"code":"minute","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" must be between 0 and 59."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"seconds","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" must be at least 0.0 and must be strictly less than 60.0."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It will be rounded down to the nearest microsecond."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the given time is not representable in the given time zone (for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example, 02:30 on March 14th 2010 in Toronto, due to daylight savings"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"time) then the time will be rounded up to the nearest existing time"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(in this case, 03:00).  If this matters to you then you should verify","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the return value for containing the same as the numbers you gave."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the case that the given time is ambiguous in the given time zone"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(for example, 01:30 on November 7th 2010 in Toronto, due to daylight"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"savings time) then the time falling within standard (ie:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"non-daylight) time is taken."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It not considered a programmer error for the values to this function"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to be out of range, but in the case that they are, the function will"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"